{'text': "There's nothing inherently wrong with heroin, cocaine or marijuana. \xa0Just because we ban them doesn't mean they no longer exist."}
{'text': 'My opinion does not mean that I am right. \xa0But it does mean that I am not wrong.'}
{'text': "There's no reason why anyone should be forced to use drugs. \xa0It's a natural behavior that most of us have come to accept as part of human nature."}
{'text': "I don't think we need more drugs in our society. \xa0I think we need to stop making drugs so available and affordable, and I think we need to stop prosecuting people for using drugs."}
{'text': "Our society doesn't have the money or resources to deal with this issue."}
{'text': 'Beware of the temptation to have a free lunch.'}
{'text': 'Legalizing drugs is not the answer to the ills of our society. \xa0Legalization makes the problem worse.'}
{'text': "Is it really necessary to legalize drugs in the first place? \xa0Maybe if we legalize drugs completely, then there wouldn't be any money being put back into the social safety net."}
{'text': "What if people weren't punished for their actions? \xa0Wouldn't that result in a lot more innovation? \xa0What if everyone could make their own money and become their own boss?"}
{'text': 'What do you think is going to happen if we legalize drugs? Will it lead to less drug abuse?'}
{'text': "I'd rather live in a society where there aren't so many drugs than one where there are so many drugs."}
{'text': 'For people who are addicted to drugs, this is the most effective way for them to deal with their disease.'}
{'text': 'We should not legalize drugs, but we should decriminalize them.'}
{'text': 'What if the government was to legalize all drugs? Would it also eliminate the criminal element that would inevitably be involved in dealing drugs?'}
{'text': 'Do you really think that it will make people feel safe?'}
{'text': "The government shouldn't be in the business of regulating how people use drugs. \xa0Society should be in charge of this, not the government."}
{'text': 'Drug legalization would not solve the drug abuse problem.'}
{'text': "Isn't it easier to just get rid of the laws against using drugs? \xa0Doesn't that make it a lot easier to deal with the problem?"}
{'text': 'Is it really such a bad thing to legalize drugs? To me, it seems to be a step in the right direction.'}
{'text': 'If we legalize drugs, what are we going to do with our prisons?'}
{'text': 'We should not put people in jail for having consensual sex.'}
{'text': "If you don't want to use drugs, don't use them. \xa0That's all there is to it."}
{'text': 'If people want to use drugs, they should be able to.'}
{'text': "Why not do it for alcohol? \xa0What about gambling? \xa0Aren't those activities just as addicting as drugs? \xa0How about sex?"}
{'text': 'Eliminating restrictions on the sale of drugs would make the illegal drug trade more efficient.'}
{'text': "We need to be careful that any drug legalization doesn't lead to decreased drug use. \xa0A very small number of people can lead to widespread drug use."}
{'text': 'It would probably be a good idea to reduce the amount of people who get arrested for drugs, either by decriminalization or by reducing the severity of the penalties.'}
